Create Cases for Inbound Calls with an Omni-Channel Flow Template

Save yourself time setting up this routing logic by using the Basic Routing with Case Creation template. This template identifies the caller, routes the call to a queue, creates a case for the call, and screen-pops the new case record when the agent accepts the call.

Available in: Lightning Experience, Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions with the Service Cloud

To create a flow from this template:

1. Go to Setup > Process Automation > Flows.
2. Click New Flow.
3. Select Omni-Channel Flow and click Create.
4. Select Voice Calls Routed to Basic Queue with Case Creation and click Create.
5. Open the Route Work action, remove Phone, search for and select Phone again, and click Done.
6. Save the Omni-Channel flow and activate the updates.

In Amazon Connect:

1. Open the Sample SCV Basic Routing with Case Creation contact flow.
2. Double-click the Invoke AWS Lambda function block, add the flowDevName and fallbackQueue input parameters, and save the changes.
3. Publish the Sample SCV Inbound Flow and assign it to a phone channel.
4. Assign the Sample SCV Basic Routing with Case Creation Omni-Channel flow to the phone channel.

After completing these steps, you can route calls made to a phone channel using the Sample SCV Basic Routing with Case Creation Omni-Channel flow.
